A lightbox/imagezoomer with no javascript, just css3 and html5. It makes use of css3 transforms, transitions, and the css focus pseudo-class. It also uses to html5 contenteditable attribute.

Instrutions for the plugin:
1) link to the plugin.css code like this: <link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/plugin.css" />
2) structure the images you want affected like this:
	<figure class="lightbox inline" contenteditable="true">
		<img src="images/example.png" alt="example image" />
		<figcaption>Example</figcaption>
	</figure>
3) If the images you want affected aren't supposed to be part of the text, remove the inline class from the figure element.
4) just add css after the plugin is loaded to customize the appearance of images